he's not even a member of the Klan.

694
01:11:19,951 --> 01:11:24,956
Objection? This is just an interview, sir.
There's really no need to be so formal.

695
01:11:25,165 --> 01:11:31,526
Well, if this is just an interview, I guess
I don't have to stay here. I got work to do.

696
01:11:33,612 --> 01:11:38,096
- I guess you do too, don't you?
- Yes, sir. You can be sure that we'll do it.

697
01:11:38,722 --> 01:11:40,808
Good luck.

698
01:11:41,851 --> 01:11:46,543
Y'all get enough to indict me,
you know where to find me.

699
01:11:48,733 --> 01:11:50,610
- How'd it go?
- Fine. Just fine.

700
01:11:50,610 --> 01:11:53,218
Don't you worry about a goddamn thing.

701
01:11:54,260 --> 01:11:56,242
Are you about to be indicted?

702
01:11:56,346 --> 01:11:59,370
Does the FBI have evidence
against the sheriff's office?

703
01:11:59,370 --> 01:12:03,333
- Are you cooperating with them?
- We're cooperatin'. We have all along.

704
01:12:03,438 --> 01:12:05,419
There's not one iota of proof.

705
01:12:05,419 --> 01:12:09,486
Could you not do that, please?
Sir, do not do that, please.

706
01:12:10,842 --> 01:12:14,075
You've already been told once!
Get the fuck outta here!

707
01:12:16,473 --> 01:12:20,019
Do we have to tell you 2,000 times?
Go back where you belong!

708
01:12:20,853 --> 01:12:23,252
Get outta my face!

709
01:12:23,356 --> 01:12:26,485
Get on outta here and leave us alone!
Leave us alone!

710
01:12:27,423 --> 01:12:30,552
Go on home where you belong, boy!
You're gonna get hurt!

711
01:12:33,055 --> 01:12:36,287
Mr Ward, this is gettin' to be
about as much as we can take.

712
01:12:36,392 --> 01:12:39,312
- I cannot register a stronger complaint.
- Not now, sir.

713
01:12:39,416 --> 01:12:44,213
Now, just a minute. I resent your
public pursuit of my sheriff's department.

714
01:12:44,213 --> 01:12:47,967
You have made every effort to
implicate them in these disappearances.

715
01:12:47,967 --> 01:12:52,869
Your slimy innuendoes are not evidence
that they were connected with any crime.

716
01:12:52,973 --> 01:12:55,789
We're trying to get to the truth.
We're frustrated too.

717
01:12:55,893 --> 01:12:59,230
Any jackass can point a finger,
but that ain't evidence.

718
01:12:59,334 --> 01:13:03,506
Us old cotton-choppers are still
stupid enough to believe in democracy.

719
01:13:03,610 --> 01:13:08,199
- We know our rights under the law!
- You know somethin', all right.

720
01:13:08,303 --> 01:13:13,413
- I'd bet a cotton-choppin' dollar on that.
- You're gettin' so far up my nose...

721
01:13:13,517 --> 01:13:16,437
...I'm beginnin' to feel
your boots on my chin.

722
01:13:16,541 --> 01:13:19,461
And I'm tellin' you one more time,
Mr Apple Red.

723
01:13:19,461 --> 01:13:24,154
A couple of crazies in bedsheets dancin'
round the countryside scarin' Negroes...

724
01:13:24,259 --> 01:13:27,179
...is not the fault of the entire
state of Mississippi!

725
01:13:27,283 --> 01:13:32,914
There are three dead kids and a lot of
scared people because of your sheriff.

726
01:13:33,018 --> 01:13:38,754
- So get used to havin' us around.
- Get used to my boots on your chin too.

727
01:13:38,858 --> 01:13:40,944
And you people better back off.

728
01:13:42,300 --> 01:13:46,993
Goddamn FBI. Who do they think they are,
comin' to my part of the country...

729
01:13:47,097 --> 01:13:50,538
- Do you have a statement, Mr Mayor?
- Goddamn right I have.

730
01:13:50,643 --> 01:13:53,458
For a moment there, Mr Anderson...

731
01:13:53,458 --> 01:13:56,587
...it sounded like we were
both on the same side.

732
01:14:24,431 --> 01:14:27,038
- Are you all right, honey?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

733
01:14:27,142 --> 01:14:30,375
- Let me know if you need anything.
- Thanks. I will.

734
01:15:54,951 --> 01:15:56,619
Momma! Come quick!

735
01:16:13,200 --> 01:16:16,329
There's no sign of him, sir.
He's long gone.

736
01:16:16,433 --> 01:16:20,188
His mother lives across the street.
She won't even answer the door.

737
01:16:20,292 --> 01:16:23,838
I want the whole area covered.
Someone must have seen something.

738
01:16:23,942 --> 01:16:26,236
- They won't talk to us.
- Get going, Mr Bird.

739
01:16:26,340 --> 01:16:29,052
If they won't talk to us, shake it out of 'em.

740
01:16:32,389 --> 01:16:34,892
Let's go. Every house. Come on.

741
01:16:41,983 --> 01:16:43,756
What?

742
01:16:43,860 --> 01:16:49,492
All these white guys chasin' around with
their notebooks will get you nowhere.

743
01:16:49,596 --> 01:16:52,307
<i>OK. What would you do?</i>

744
01:16:57,626 --> 01:17:00,024
It's OK to be afraid.

745
01:17:07,846 --> 01:17:12,017
Go on, Willie. Tell 'em what you saw.

746
01:17:45,910 --> 01:17:48,726
The defendants will rise.

747
01:17:51,646 --> 01:17:54,774
In this country a man's home is his castle.

748
01:17:56,026 --> 01:18:00,614
That is one of the principles
by which this community survives.

749
01:18:00,718 --> 01:18:03,847
You men have done violence
to that principle.

750
01:18:03,951 --> 01:18:06,976
But I want you to know
that the court understands...

751
01:18:07,080 --> 01:18:11,564
...that the crimes you have committed
have been, to some extent at least...

752
01:18:11,668 --> 01:18:15,423
...brought about by... outside influences.

753
01:18:24,391 --> 01:18:27,520
Outsiders have come
into Jessup County...

754
01:18:27,520 --> 01:18:31,900
...and they've been
people of low morality...

755
01:18:32,004 --> 01:18:34,507
...and unhygienic.

756
01:18:34,924 --> 01:18:38,261
And their presence here
has provoked a lot of people.

757
01:18:40,973 --> 01:18:43,162
So the court understands...

758
01:18:43,162 --> 01:18:46,917
...without condoning them, mind you...

759
01:18:46,917 --> 01:18:50,045
...that the crimes to which
you men have pled guilty...

760
01:18:50,150 --> 01:18:55,677
...were, to some extent at least,
provoked by these outside influences.

761
01:18:58,180 --> 01:19:02,560
So, with all this,
I'm gonna make your punishment light.

762
01:19:03,602 --> 01:19:08,191
I'm gonna sentence you each
to five years' imprisonment.

763
01:19:11,319 --> 01:19:13,822
But I'm gonna suspend these sentences.

764
01:19:48,549 --> 01:19:51,052
You can't go in there, sir.

765
01:19:51,156 --> 01:19:53,242
FBI. Let us through.

766
01:19:53,346 --> 01:19:55,745
I'm sorry, sir. You can't go in there.

767
01:20:01,168 --> 01:20:03,253
Sheriff?

768
01:20:06,486 --> 01:20:08,885
Y'all really started somethin' this time.

769
01:20:08,989 --> 01:20:11,492
Move these cars.
I wanna go in and talk to them.

770
01:20:11,596 --> 01:20:15,038
- You've gone as far as you're gonna go.
- We can handle this.

771
01:20:15,142 --> 01:20:18,062
Just some crazy coloureds
tearin' up their own assholes.

772
01:20:18,166 --> 01:20:20,252
Local problem.

773
01:20:36,208 --> 01:20:40,588
Look at those flames, Mr Ward. That's
why they sent you down here, wasn't it?

774
01:20:41,213 --> 01:20:44,655
It would've happened anyway
and you know it.

775
01:20:45,906 --> 01:20:49,452
If I was a Negro,
I'd probably think the same way they do.

776
01:20:49,973 --> 01:20:54,145
If you were a Negro,
nobody'd give a damn what you thought.

777
01:21:51,084 --> 01:21:55,673
Aaron! Take your momma, grandmomma
and the children out the back door.

778
01:21:55,673 --> 01:22:00,053
When you hit the road, keep goin'.
You understand? Keep goin', son.

779
01:22:01,721 --> 01:22:04,120
Nathan! Come on, Nathan. Get up!

780
01:22:04,224 --> 01:22:07,353
Get up, Nathan, now! Come on!
Get out of the bed!

781
01:22:07,353 --> 01:22:11,941
- What's happening?
- Momma! Come on, Momma.

782
01:22:14,548 --> 01:22:16,634
Come on, y'all.

783
01:22:17,468 --> 01:22:20,180
Come on, Grandma. Let's go!

784
01:22:28,210 --> 01:22:35,927
<i># All ye who labour</i>

785
01:22:36,344 --> 01:22:41,350
Who's there? If you're in there,
come on out! You hear?

786
01:22:42,184 --> 01:22:44,374
I ain't takin' this shit no more!

787
01:22:59,287 --> 01:23:07,630
<i># Bring him your burdens</i>

788
01:23:09,194 --> 01:23:15,034
<i># Seek not his favour</i>

789
01:23:15,764 --> 01:23:23,898
<i># Tell... tell him your sorrows</i>

790
01:23:25,358 --> 01:23:35,787
<i># In... him... confide</i>

791
01:23:38,394 --> 01:23:42,357
<i># He satisfies</i>

792
01:23:43,191 --> 01:23:47,049
<i># He satisfies</i>

793
01:23:49,344 --> 01:23:51,325
Everything's OK, Papa.

794
01:23:51,742 --> 01:23:53,828
Momma and the giris are fine.

795
01:23:53,932 --> 01:23:57,374
They just cracked your head some.
You just keep on breathin'.

796
01:23:57,478 --> 01:23:59,668
Don't you go dyin' on me now.

797
01:23:59,876 --> 01:24:01,962
You hear me?

798
01:24:03,214 --> 01:24:05,195
You gonna be just fine.

799
01:24:32,101 --> 01:24:37,211
You know, cows won't run away. No one
knows why. They're just stupid, I guess.

800
01:24:37,315 --> 01:24:42,946
They just stand there until
their bellies swell up and they pop.

801
01:24:43,050 --> 01:24:45,866
They have relatives in Detroit.

802
01:24:46,596 --> 01:24:50,142
- Are they gonna go?
- I didn't give 'em any choice.

803
01:24:51,706 --> 01:24:54,835
At least we know who did this.

804
01:24:54,939 --> 01:24:57,755
- We did.
- Well, don't fret. It's progress.

805
01:24:57,859 --> 01:25:02,239
20 years ago they'd have
strung 'em up for stealin' a watermelon.

806
01:25:02,343 --> 01:25:05,785
I don't understand you, Mr Anderson.
Not at all.

807
01:25:07,140 --> 01:25:09,643
Let's get somethin' straight, all right?

808
01:25:09,747 --> 01:25:13,815
This thing was fucked up the moment
we turned it into a show for the newsmen.

809
01:25:13,919 --> 01:25:16,526
<i>The moment those three kids
disappeared, it was news.</i>

810
01:25:16,630 --> 01:25:21,010
The moment the three civil rights
workers disappeared, it was news.

811
01:25:21,115 --> 01:25:24,452
To me they're just kids.
They're still missin'.

812
01:25:24,556 --> 01:25:29,145
What's missing... is the 50 minutes
Pell said he was with his wife.

813
01:25:33,003 --> 01:25:35,089
OK.

814
01:25:50,732 --> 01:25:53,652
I love Mississippi.

815
01:26:04,393 --> 01:26:06,166
They...

816
01:26:06,270 --> 01:26:08,564
They hate Mississippi.

817
01:26:09,399 --> 01:26:13,153
They hate us because
we present a shining example...

818
01:26:13,257 --> 01:26:16,490
...of successful segregation.

819
01:26:16,594 --> 01:26:21,183
These Northern students,
with their atheist, communist bosses...

820
01:26:21,183 --> 01:26:25,354
...that have come into our community
this summer with the wish to destroy it...

821
01:26:25,458 --> 01:26:29,108
...this week have taken a terrible blow.

822
01:26:29,943 --> 01:26:33,593
This week their cause has been crippled.

823
01:26:33,697 --> 01:26:38,494
This week all of these federal policemen
you see out here pryin' into our lives...

824
01:26:38,598 --> 01:26:40,580
...violatin' our civil liberties...

825
01:26:40,684 --> 01:26:43,500
...have learned that they are
powerless against us...

826
01:26:43,604 --> 01:26:49,131
...if every single Anglo-Saxon
Christian one of us stands together!

827
01:26:54,450 --> 01:26:55,701
This week...

828
01:26:57,161 --> 01:26:59,560
- Ward?
- We have company, sir.

829
01:27:00,707 --> 01:27:03,105
Why are you here?
This is a political meeting.

830
01:27:03,105 --> 01:27:07,381
- Doesn't smell that way to me, Deputy.
- It's a political meeting, Hoover boy.

831
01:27:07,485 --> 01:27:13,117
Oh, it looks like a political meeting
but smells more like Klan to me...

832
01:27:13,117 --> 01:27:16,454
...with or without the Halloween costumes.

833
01:27:17,184 --> 01:27:18,957
Gentlemen.

834
01:27:18,957 --> 01:27:22,607
In the courts of Mississippi,
they have been reminded...

835
01:27:22,711 --> 01:27:25,944
...that they cannot by force
turn our communities...

836
01:27:26,048 --> 01:27:28,551
<i>...into replicas of their communities.</i>

837
01:27:28,655 --> 01:27:33,140
Communities in which Negroes run riot,
unrestrained and unpunished...

838
01:27:33,140 --> 01:27:37,520
...as they do this summer in the streets
of Harlem, or in the streets of Oakland...

839
01:27:37,624 --> 01:27:39,814
...or in the streets of Chicago!

840
01:29:01,052 --> 01:29:03,346
Can I come in?

841
01:29:11,793 --> 01:29:13,983
It's not good for you to be here.

842
01:29:14,088 --> 01:29:16,799
- Why?
- It's ugly.

843
01:29:17,633 --> 01:29:19,928
This whole thing is so ugly.

844
01:29:20,970 --> 01:29:24,725
Have you any idea what it's like
to live with all this?

845
01:29:25,663 --> 01:29:30,252
People look at us...
and only see bigots and racists.

846
01:29:32,442 --> 01:29:35,570
Hatred isn't something you're born with.

847
01:29:35,675 --> 01:29:37,760
It gets taught.

848
01:29:39,533 --> 01:29:43,496
At school they said segregation
is what it said in the Bible.

849
01:29:44,852 --> 01:29:48,710
Genesis 9, verse 27.

850
01:29:51,943 --> 01:29:56,844
At seven years of age, you get
told it enough times, you believe it.

851
01:29:58,826 --> 01:30:01,016
You believe the hatred.

852
01:30:02,059 --> 01:30:05,709
You live it. You breathe it.

853
01:30:07,899 --> 01:30:09,984
You marry it.

854
01:30:40,331 --> 01:30:42,938
My husband drove
one of the cars that night.

855
01:30:43,043 --> 01:30:46,484
- Shh.
- That's what you wanna hear, isn't it?

856
01:30:48,361 --> 01:30:53,471
The bodies are buried
on the Roberts farm, in an earthen dam.

857
01:31:12,138 --> 01:31:13,807
Sir!

858
01:31:26,530 --> 01:31:28,824
Take a break, Mr Bird.

859
01:31:28,928 --> 01:31:31,640
Put some handkerchiefs around your face.

860
01:31:44,988 --> 01:31:47,074
Bring that here.

861
01:32:01,465 --> 01:32:05,011
The bodies of the three civil rights
workers were found today...

862
01:32:05,011 --> 01:32:07,409
...at an undisclosed grave.

863
01:32:08,869 --> 01:32:13,354
Neither the FBI nor the sheriff's
department will comment on the case.

864
01:32:13,458 --> 01:32:16,274
The bodies were brought
to Jessup County Hospital.

865
01:32:16,274 --> 01:32:18,777
Officials here also refused comment.

866
01:32:18,881 --> 01:32:23,261
There is speculation that an autopsy
will be performed later tonight.

867
01:32:25,346 --> 01:32:28,266
OK, keep it open. We're comin' through.

868
01:32:28,371 --> 01:32:30,978
Come on, open it up.

869
01:32:32,125 --> 01:32:34,002
Hold it back.

870
01:32:53,921 --> 01:32:56,841
Clinton,
you got problems at home to tend to.

871
01:32:56,945 --> 01:32:58,405
What do you mean?

872
01:32:58,509 --> 01:33:02,159
I mean pull your head
out of your ass and get home!

873
01:33:02,263 --> 01:33:06,748
<i>"I, Vincent Thompson, am the
cheddar-cheese champion of the worid."</i>

874
01:33:07,999 --> 01:33:13,422
<i>"In international competition with 42 other
entries, my cheddar won first prize...</i>

875
01:33:13,526 --> 01:33:17,280
<i>... based on flavour, texture,
appearance and colour."</i>

876
01:33:22,182 --> 01:33:25,936
Hey, Clinton.
I didn't expect you home so early.

877
01:33:27,188 --> 01:33:29,273
Hi, Frank.

878
01:33:39,910 --> 01:33:42,205
No, don't. I'm sorry.

879
01:33:55,970 --> 01:33:58,056
Sir.

880
01:34:00,142 --> 01:34:02,227
Say again?

881
01:34:03,583 --> 01:34:05,669
I'll be right there.

882
01:34:10,466 --> 01:34:12,864
- Mr Bird.
- Yes, sir?

883
01:34:12,864 --> 01:34:14,950
Get five men and meet me outside.

884
01:34:17,349 --> 01:34:20,477
- Where's Anderson?
- He's at the motel, sir.

885
01:34:25,170 --> 01:34:29,237
You two take the front door. If anyone
tries to get past you, break 'em down.

886
01:34:29,342 --> 01:34:32,262
You two take the door on the corridor.
Mr Bird?

887
01:34:34,034 --> 01:34:37,997
OK. Go get Anderson. Bring him here.

888
01:34:38,101 --> 01:34:42,899
Don't tell him why.
Don't tell him anything. Just get him here.

889
01:35:14,184 --> 01:35:16,478
Mr Anderson. Stop!

890
01:35:16,478 --> 01:35:18,147
- Mr Anderson!
- Go to hell.

891
01:35:18,251 --> 01:35:21,797
I'm telling you to stop and
I mean it. We're not killers.

892
01:35:21,901 --> 01:35:25,968
<i>- It's the difference between them and us.
- No, between them and you!</i>

893
01:35:26,073 --> 01:35:28,471
- You're no more like them than I am.
- Wrong.

894
01:35:28,575 --> 01:35:32,121
What do you care what I do to a bastard
hidin' behind a sheriff's badge?

895
01:35:32,225 --> 01:35:35,354
- You have the whole worid to change!
- And I'm changin' it.

896
01:35:35,458 --> 01:35:39,004
- You're as arrogant as you are stupid!
- You're changin' it too.

897
01:35:39,108 --> 01:35:41,090
I'll make some changes right now!

898
01:35:41,194 --> 01:35:45,574
Don't mess this up just because
you like foolin' around with witnesses.

899
01:35:55,377 --> 01:35:57,567
A gun don't mean shit unless you use it.

900
01:35:57,671 --> 01:36:01,842
- I'll kill you now if you don't listen to me.
- Fuck you.

901
01:36:01,947 --> 01:36:04,032
Let me go. Let me go.

902
01:36:06,327 --> 01:36:10,707
- We'll go after all of 'em, together.
- You wouldn't know how!

903
01:36:10,811 --> 01:36:13,418
- You'll teach me.
- You don't have the guts.

904
01:36:13,522 --> 01:36:16,755
Not only do I have the guts,
I have the authority.

905
01:36:16,859 --> 01:36:18,945
What is that supposed to mean?

906
01:36:19,049 --> 01:36:24,159
New rules. We nail 'em any way we can.
Even your way.

907
01:36:24,264 --> 01:36:27,184
Is this you talkin' or
some guy pullin' your strings?

908
01:36:27,288 --> 01:36:29,269
Both.

909
01:36:29,374 --> 01:36:31,459
- We do it my way.
- Your way.

910
01:36:31,564 --> 01:36:34,275
- With my people!
- Whatever it takes.

911
01:36:36,152 --> 01:36:38,029
OK.

912
01:36:44,078 --> 01:36:46,164
Gimme a minute.

913
01:36:53,881 --> 01:36:56,801
- You think he would've shot me?
- Oh, yes, sir.

914
01:36:58,052 --> 01:37:00,555
He's a ballsy little bastard, isn't he?

915
01:37:08,585 --> 01:37:11,192
They want me to say "Let us not forget...

916
01:37:11,192 --> 01:37:16,302
...that two white boys also died
helping Negroes help themselves."

917
01:37:19,431 --> 01:37:24,749
They want me to say "We mourn with
the mothers of these two white boys."

918
01:37:27,982 --> 01:37:32,362
But the state of Mississippi
won't even allow these white boys...

919
01:37:32,466 --> 01:37:36,012
...to be buried in the same
cemetery as this Negro boy.

920
01:37:38,723 --> 01:37:42,999
<i>I say I have no more love to give.</i>

